review_body: Call connection is clear, but the sound quality isnâ€™t the best. The speaker is at the bottom of the phone and sounds fuzzy/muffled even on high volume. Headphones or a Bluetooth speaker are highly recommended for music. HD video playback can be laggy, especially without a good WiFi connection. The battery is terrible and needs to be charged daily if the phone is being used regularly. Conveniently, the L1 comes with a battery saver and data saver option that really help with the bad battery life. The slide the SIM card fits into is quite difficult to pull out. The manual says use your fingernails to pry the slide out, but I could not do this without tweezers. Aesthetically, the L1 is pretty. Rectangular, but with rounded edges, similar to the old Nokia Lumia phones. Itâ€™s also lightweight but the materials are on the cheap side, and the screen most definitely cracks if dropped in a parking lot.  Overall, this is an excellent value-priced smart phone with decent visual appeal.

product_name: Sony Xperia L1 - Unlocked Smartphone - 16GB - Black (US Warranty)
review_title: Good value with some premium features
review_body: Pros:Camera is slightly above expectationsNo bloatwareAndroid 7.0 Nougat, With November 2017 Security UpdatePerformance (for price point)Screen sizeConstruction is all plastic, but very durableNFCUSB-C PortCons:No fingerprint sensorFace scanner doesn't work in low-light conditionsWill not receive Android OreoDoes not include quick charger in the boxOverall, I am very happy with the phone, especially at this price point.  I believe this is one of the best value smartphones currently out, assuming you are not a power user. Sony is typically generous with software and security updates, but this phone will not be receiving Android 8.0 Oreo.The display on this phone is 5.5 inches, putting it in the size category of flagship phones. However, the screen resolution is only HD 720p, which is quite a bit below the pixel density of flagship phones. However, Sony is using a very good screen on this phone, with great white balance and viewing angles.I'm using the phone on AT&T, and it has full connectivity over LTE. The lack of a fingerprint sensor is an annoyance, but that is a reasonable sacrifice for such a good value. Facial recognition seems to work fine for me in well-lit areas, but does not work at all in low-light situations.Performance is what you'd expect for this class of phone - there are occasional stutters, but they don't hamper day-to-day use. Battery charges quickly with a quick charger, but the charger included in the box works at a standard, slow speed. The phone seems to hold a charge all day with normal use, which is in part due to the lower resolution screen.  This phone includes support for NFC, which is quite rare at this price point. This allows you to use Android Pay in stores, as well as share files with other NFC-supporting phones.This phone is a great value at this price point, especially if you want USB-C and a large screen, but do not want a flagship. If you are looking for sheer amount of features, there may be better options at this price point. Sony quality, in my experience, is worth a small price premium.

product_name: Vitagene DNA Test Kit:  Ancestry + Health Personal Genetic Reports
review_title: Best DNA kit with add on insights!!
review_body: I have been wanting to look into my DNA for months now, ever since the fad has hit the market. I thought that I would just want to know my background, but this DNA kit is much more than just finding out your genetics. This DNA kit gave me an insight of everything that I needed to know regarding my genetics and health profiles.I had my first baby over 6 months ago and have been having a hard time losing this baby weight. It has never been an issue for me to lose weight, in fact I have been thin most of my life, so this added weight put a damper on my mood, especially when dieting and exercising was not helping. After utilizing this DNA kit, and finding out more about my body, it has helped me find out what I need to do with my diet plans to help me lose this baby weight. Since changing my dieting rituals to coincide with my genetics, it has helped me lose weight and get back into my pre-baby weight and clothes!This kit was so easy to use. All you have to do is take the swaps, swap each check, and put the swabs into the vials given. Plus, it comes with a pre-paid box to send back to the lab.Overall, this DNA kit has given me much more insights about my genetics than I thought it could. It is well worth the price tag, when you look into the lifelong information it gives you about your genetics.

product_name: Vitagene DNA Test Kit:  Ancestry + Health Personal Genetic Reports
review_body: Wow. TOTAL waste of money. As a previous commenter noted, the health/wellness information could have come from a 7th grade Health textbook. Considering I answered a VERY long questionnaire for them AND they HAVE MY DNA, for goodness' sake, the report was extremely generic and unhelpful. Even considering all the information I gave them -- for one example, weight training 3 times a week -- my daily protein recommendation was 46 grams. I am a small female, but for anyone who knows the LEAST LITTLE BIT about nutrition, that will barely help me maintain enough muscle to get out of bed in the morning, not to mention I'm 47 yoa and we need more protein as we age for bone health. It's actually laughable if I hadn't paid them for something I didn't get. The health/wellness portion is lacking SO much, it makes me doubt that the ancestry portion is even true. If you get nothing else from this review, please heed this warning--DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY!! Just pay more money for a company like DNAfit.

product_name: Vitagene DNA Test Kit:  Ancestry + Health Personal Genetic Reports
review_body: When you receive the kit, the first thing you need to do is activate it online using a unique code posted on the kit. The code is used to keep your sample anonymous but trackable throughout the process. Next, you fill in your information on the Vitagene webpage and answer a few questions related to lifestyle. Once you've finished activating your kit and setting up your account, it's time to extract your sample, which involves scrapping the insides of both (mouth) cheeks with the provided swabs and placing them in the appropriate plastic tubes (also provided). The last step is to shake the tubes for about five seconds, place them in the collection bag, put the bag in the prepaid shipping box and then drop it off at the Post office. You can't eat, drink or smoke within 30 minutes of collecting samples. The whole process is quick and painless.Results can take a few weeks to receive considering the amount of information being gathered. Therefore, this is somewhat of a general review as I am still in the process for receiving mine and will update after looking them over. The Vitagene DNA Test Kit was affordable relative to others like it, so I figured it was worth a go and so far I'm impressed with how easy the process has been.

product_name: Vitagene DNA Test Kit:  Ancestry + Health Personal Genetic Reports

I don't diet but I do try to eat healthy.I submitted the dna test kit and am waiting for my results.  You take a very quick questionnaire and when the results come in, you will get diet, exercise and supplement reports, in addition to the genetic and ancestry reports.  I'm so excited to see what the diet and exercise reports have to say- do I need a different fitness regime? Do I need to steer clear of certain foods or add certain supplements?Do I metabolize carbohydrates more slowly than others?  With this helpful information I can make smart choices and make lasting changes for my health!

product_name: Vitagene DNA Test Kit:  Ancestry + Health Personal Genetic Reports
review_body: My family and I have been talking about the DNA test kits. I have been wanting to order one but it is difficult to pick between them. I saw this Vitagene DNA test kit and thought it was interesting because it had a lot of health-related testing and evaluation that it does. I went ahead and ordered the kit and it was here and only 2 days, thanks to Amazon Prime.I opened the kit to read the instructions. When I did so I noticed one of the two vials was empty. There are two vials you are supposed to put your samples in and they have a solution in them. However one vial had a loose cap. It had leaked all over the inside of the box. I called Vitagene and requested a replacement vial, but they said it was not critical that there be two samples. They provide two vials so if one sample is contaminated they have a second one. They said I should just go ahead and do the sample and send it in. I assume if the sample is not usable they will then send me two more vials. Kind of a pain, but I understand it is not practical for them to send another vial if they rarely need to rely on the second vial.Taking the sample was pretty easy. I just had to use the swabs on the inside of my cheeks, first the left than the right.  The kit includes a prepaid label on a small box and an envelope to seal the samples inside of to place in the Box. I did tape the box closed because there was no seal for the box and I was concerned it might crush and open in shipment.I also went online to the Vitagene website to register the sample.  Each of the two vials and the instruction card have a sample number on it. This number is used to register the sample in advance. It appears that they will notify me once the sample is received and processed. In looking at their website it looks like there is a wealth of information I will get once the sample is processed.For the moment I am optimistic that the sample will process fine and I will get some great information. I have only provided a four star rating because I'm disappointed at the sample vile being open and the fact that now I have to be concerned that the one sample will not be valid and there is no backup. Once I get my results I will update this review if necessary to increase or decrease the star rating.

review_body: I didn't know what to expect when purchasing this product but I really glad that I did. It's so much more than a DNA Ancestry Kit. The packaging it came in was of high quality. The process was short and simple and the instructions made everything really easy to follow. All you have to do is swab placed in a tube and off they went. I was surprised that not only did they provide DNA background and Ancestry reports but also a chart showing my current health. I definitely recommend purchasing this product.

product_name: Vitagene DNA Test Kit:  Ancestry + Health Personal Genetic Reports
review_title: It's Worth Your Life...but BE INFORMED!
review_body: At first, I was super disappointed in this product. The information I got was "technically" based off my DNA, but was extremely surface level in every way (with ancestry and health). So, I ended up taking the raw DNA file they gave me and ran it through Promethius for $10, which gave me IN DEPTH explanations as to what my DNA says. After reading my review, a guy from Vitagene gave me a call. We had an awesome and productive conversation, at the end of which, I got my money back. In that light, I decided to update my review so that you can be truly informed as you make a decision about Vitagene. Here's what you should know:1. REACH OUT TO VITAGENE FIRST: Email them at support@vitagene.com, ask your questions and request a phone call. It's worth the hassle, believe me. Vitagene heard me when I told them how disappointed I was that I got shallow information back and explained why I used Promethius, etc. The guy I talked to (who was great) stated that they are in the process now of trying to develop what Promethius does, which is essentially give detailed explanations to customers about what their DNA says and what it means. So, before you buy, call and talk to their people. Ask them where they are in their product development and how much information you'll actually receive that's tailored to your DNA. THE INFORMATION IS WORTH IT if you can get all of it. It'll be worth the wait if you need to wait.2. UNDERSTAND DNA + TALK WITH YOUR DOCTOR: When I checked my DNA against Promethius, I understood why Vitagene recommended the vitamins they did. Their recommendations were SPOT ON! But this was a double-edged sword. The recommendation came out of potential future/some present health risks coded in my DNA. (Almost like finding out what you might die of). It was hard to read, but super inspiring for someone who has always struggled to eat well. I found myself suddenly motivated! I looked over what Promethius wrote up, made a list of my risks, took it to my doctor and was told that 90% of everyone carries those risks in their DNA (huh...). We're all basically walking around like loaded guns and our lifestyle and diet pull the trigger. The better you understand how your body responds to those things, the better you can avoid that trigger. So, when you get the information from Vitagene, take it to your doctor. Mine looked over the list of vitamin recommendations, affirmed some and cautioned others. She also affirmed my risk list stating that if I feel weird at any given time, we can refer to it and go directly to blood tests instead of guessing for 6-12months and trying again. Super helpful! ...SO while Vitagene didn't get me all the way there, if that's where they're headed, this product is worth your life.The reason I got Vitagene was because I wanted to understand my body better instead of mindlessly eating food and hoping that some form of exercise worked along with some vague idea of what healthy was. I want to do everything I can to not only live long, but live well, and avoid taking drugs for things that a better, DNA-tailored lifestyle can address. This is also Vitagene's goal and an honorable one at that.

I was told that the DNA  tested part of the heritage.Talking to a non-robot was nearly impossible. The account # that I was given did not work. When I finally lied in order to talk to a human to "order a kit", I was told that they tried the # and it did not work and they did not know why...and that on Sunday the lab would call me,  which they never did because their lab is in Israel  and there is a 10 hour difference...I did send them 3 emails...with no response.

product_name: Family Tree DNA Genetic Ancestry Test Kit - Worlds First Genetic Genealogy Company - History Unearthed Daily
review_title: I've been sorely disappointed in the results
review_body: I ordered the Family Tree Y-DNA test in hopes of tracing my paternal line back past my GG Grandfather.  I've been sorely disappointed in the results.  Not only is the test shrouded in all sorts of DNA jargon, it provided no discernible links to my  family tree.  The matches that were shown for my DNA either had very sketchy family trees posted on Family Tree, or, in most cases, no family tree at all.  Evidently no one in my lineage has taken the test to try to connect as I did.  While it gives higher probabilities of connecting back 15 generations or so, that does me no good.  I've also taken the Ancestry.com and was much more satisfied with the results.  Family Tree was a waste of time, money, and q-tips!

product_name: Family Tree DNA Genetic Ancestry Test Kit - Worlds First Genetic Genealogy Company - History Unearthed Daily
review_body: I've tested with Ancestry, My Heritage and uploaded results to GEDmatch. After uploading to Family Tree DNA, by comparison they seem the least accurate and overly generalized if you are hoping to find detailed ethnicity. I paid for My Origins and the results were surprising in a strange way. Much of my family heritage can be traced to west Europe in the region of where France, Switzerland and Germany border each other, yet FT DNA shows 0% in this region. I can only guess that this region was either lumped into British Isles or Eastern European.Another comparison is the British Isles:Family Tree DNA 43%My Heritage 5.6%Ancestry (combining England/Ireland regions) 13%GEDmatch is 24.5% (combining the N. Atlantic and North Sea regions).Being able to trace a branch of my ancestors back to England and Scotland to the 1500's, I'd say Ancestry and GEDmatch (Eurogenes K36) are probably the most accurate. Family Tree DNA seemed to get 3 other regions correct, however two of my big ones were very wrong. Although I did not buy the whole kit on Amazon, only paid for My Origins online I felt I should review here as I find Amazon reviews helpful. If you want to use this kit to find relatives, cousins, etc matching your DNA then Family Tree DNA may be a good choice, but would not recommend them for your ethnicity.

product_name: Meow Mix Tender Centers, 13.5-Pound, Salmon & Chicken
review_title: Good taste... awful results. Cat got sick!
review_body: Iâ€™m fairly new to this â€˜cat momâ€™ thing, and of course we all want the best for our fur babies. Being a new mom, I wish I had done significantly more research before buying this food... let me save you the trouble.I bought 3 large bags of the Tender Centers Salmon cat food when it was a really good deal at Target. I was excited to get such a good deal on a well-known â€œreputableâ€� (I thought) brand. I gradually began mixing this food with the previous dry food we had been feeding our two boys (Purina, I think?), and eventually they were solely on this for dry food. They seemed to really enjoy the flavor, and all was well for a month or so...And then our 1 year old male cat began vomiting. Not just once or twice, more like once or twice a week. And then even more frequently... once or twice a DAY. Nothing else in his diet changed. He was and is an overall healthy and playfully active cat. At first I wrote it off in my mind as hairballs. It was quite obviously his shedding season, as he was constantly leaving hair everywhere he went. (Being a new mom, this seemed like a fair conclusion. Cats regularly get hairballs, right?) We began grooming our boy every night, even tried giving him a bath a couple of times in hopes that he would stop vomiting â€˜hairballs,â€™ but to no avail. After another month of vomiting, and a panicked night when we thought he was vomiting blood, we took him to the vet to get some answers.After hearing how we were caring for our cat and what diet changes had recently ensued, our vet strongly recommended disposing of the rest of the Meow Mix cat food. She instead recommended the Hills Science Diet Sensitive Stomach Formula for our cat.I was inclined to do a lot of research before jumping in and spending $40 on a bag of cat food the same size as the Meow Mix which I had purchased for less than $10. What I found out was scary.Many cat foods are made to taste good to the cat and look appealing for humans to feed their pets (I mean really, does a cat understand and think that colorful food is more appealing? I would say probably not... a catâ€™s color vision is similar to a human that is color blind.). Though it may taste good to your cat, it may not provide the nutrition they need. It also can have ingredients that unfortunately are harmful to your pet, such as BHA and BHT as preservatives. As mentioned above, artificial color ingredients (yellow 5, red 40, etc.) have no real benefit and serve only the purpose of adding color. Not to mention, cats by design are carnivores... they need meat! Why, then, are the first two ingredients corn product? Corn is inexpensive and is oftentimes used as filler ingredient in pet food to keep costs down and make it appealing to the consumer on a tight budget.Think of it this way, though... cheap food now probably means expensive vet bills later. Save yourself the time, frustration, and money. Make an investment in higher-quality food for your pet now.To conclude our dilemma, we discovered that the vomit that we thought contained blood ended up being the unnecessary red food coloring in the product. We made the investment (found out in the process that PetSmart matches Amazon pricing, yay!) and our boy is now munching quite happily on the brand recommended by our vet (though in all honesty, after doing my research Iâ€™m inclined to switch to Merrick: Before Grain, as it contains no grain where Hills Science Diet still does contain substantial grain).Giving credit where credit is due, I am so thankful for the research analysts who analyzed 2,443 formulas of cat food in order to help new moms (and dads) like me to make the best decisions for our fur babies. Read their results online and be enlightened. :)

product_name: MSI Gaming GeForce GTX 1080 8GB GDDR5X SLI DirectX 12 VR Ready...
review_title: Trusted Brand, Quality Product, Excellent Performance
review_body: I have been hesitant to purchase a video card because of the GPU shortage and inflated costs.  I decided to go for it and couldn't be happier.  I upgraded from an MSI R9 390 8G, which is still a very nice card, but was really lagging behind in some games.For example, I had put off playing Assassin's Creed Origins due to poor performance on the R9 390.  I had most of the settings set to low or off and it just didn't make a difference.  After installing the GTX 1080, the game automatically bumped up the settings, and the performance was vastly improved.  Not only did it look like a completely different game, it plays like a completely different game.  This has been the case for all the games I have been testing.  Ghost Recon Wildlands is another example of a massive quality and performance jump.I am new to Nvidia GPU boost, but if my understanding is correct, it will automatically boost as high as possible if power and thermals are in check.  I am currently getting a boost level of 1924 on the Core.  I don't overclock and I have not adjusting any settings to achieve this.  This card so far is a fantastic performer and stays very cool under load.  I have a more aggressive fan curve set in MSI afterburner.I have owned many MSI products over the years and have always felt they have very high quality.  When you remove the card from the packaging, it certainly has some weight and feels very sturdy.  Due to the weight, it's possible you could have to deal with some slight GPU sag.  It's actually lighter than the R9 390 I replaced which was causing sag.  There are several inexpensive ways to alleviate GPU sag.I was in need of a GPU upgrade and was waiting to see what the next Nvidia or AMD gpu is going to be "possibly" be later this year.  If and when they even release the first versions they will probably be reference only with inferior performance and cooling.  It can take a good while after that just non-reference cards hit the market.  For me, jumping in now, even though there "could" be something arriving in the near future, I couldn't be happier with my purchase.I have been supportive of team Red for many years, but AMD just isn't getting it done at the moment.  I decided that I wanted to improve my gaming experience and Nvidia is the only real option in my opinion.Highly Recommended

review_body: PROLetâ€™s talk first, this charismatic GPU tends to catch your heart and possibly not let go!! I bought my first GPU mid February, had it shipped 13th of February. Iâ€™d get another one if I neededâ€¦.. or even if I donâ€™t need it I just made a second purchase of the same exact GPU through Amazon, got it delivered 20th. BECAUSE I AM IN LOVE WITH MSI RIGHT NOW.OTHERAfter purchasing the GPU I would recommend purchasing the MSI Accessory Graphics Card Bolster. To be honest, all GPU slants, or sags. This can be fixed with a holder, or a bracket, but hey couple dollars more and you get an official bracket made especially from a company that manufactures your GPU, so they know what they are dealing with.Also, I am still mad at myself for not finding out or looking into MSI graphics card before doing the whole â€œpurchaseâ€� for my first PC because I did not get an MSI Mother board, instead I chose a different brand, and this is the worst part of my purchase. review_body: So, first of all, I know itâ€™s really late for a review, specting to 2000 series from nvidia launch this year, but, to anyone thinking on buying this card for gaming (I really donâ€™t know how well it performs when youâ€™re mining, so Iâ€™m gonna let that part aside) its a solid hardware to game in ultra, +60 fps in 1440p, Iâ€™ve tried BF1, Far Cry 5, GTA V, BF 4, Pubg (this game specially is a headache, while having al the settings in ultra, it would dip to the low 40â€™s sometimes in random moments of the match, and then come up to the 100 fps, so I decided to leave it in High settings),  Fortnite, with everything in epic, a solid 120 fps. In 4k, it shows where the card lacks in horsepower to push everything stable, and in high settings, to +60 fps, but anyway, temperatures are really good, just a couple of times (And Iâ€™ve bought this card on August 2016) going over the 80 C and fan noise is moderate to low, overall, a really good card for 1440p gaming, Iâ€™m very happy with my product and my purchase, 9/10 would buy again (9 just because the software for controlling the LEDâ€™s on the card is BS, but with that aside, is a solid card)

review_body: My Gigabyte 980 Ti G1 went to Jesus last week so I decided to upgrade to the 1080 Ti SC2. The 1080 Ti is a beast. What a frame monster. Just about every game on ultra settings with 60 fps minimum. I also did well with the silicon lottery. My card boosts to 1911 MHz out of the box stock settings. I'm sure with some oc It can reach over 2000 MHz. Very happy with the card, not so much with the price. But this card was worth it.The icx cooling also works very well at keeping the card cool. Highest temp so far was 65c in Assassin's Creed Origins with fans set to a custom fan curve in EVGA Precision XOC.

review_title: Card runs cool, never broke 65c under load with default settings
review_body: Purchased at 799.99 back on june 1st on newegg.Card runs cool, never broke 65c under load with default settings. I ended up overclocking for science and pushing 69c load with 2190 boost clock and +650 on memory.I didn't need to overclock it though so after a month I reverted to default. Card paid for itself with mining last year in about 2 months. I don't mine anymore, just felt like it to make the money back and then some.I run at 1440p and VR with the vive. I can supersample my vive to 1.8 for everything without any tweaks. I don't notice any difference past 1.8.Every game for the most part runs over 90-100+ fps at 1440p, some more, some less. ( max settings ).Amazing card and for the money at 800 bucks it's worth it.

The stock fan had a horrible "clicking" sound under heavy load, but after replacing the fan the problem was resolved (wasn't tooooooo difficult). I really do love this card, but it would have been really nice if I didn't have this issue to begin with. I'm simply too impatient to send it back, wait "5 days for processing" and then have the vendor issue a replacement/reimburse my card. I want to game NOW...

review_title: Price hike of $200 in a day, top models no longer awailable for sale or order.
review_body: I'm EVGA customer from 2010. I had GTX 580 from them, and currently I have GTX 680 4gb. I wanted to upgrade my GPU and went to EVGA website confident that I will see adequate prices. And I did. There was a FTW 3 elite version with 12gh memory for $850. Next day, when I sat down with my credit card to buy a new GPU, I saw that not only 12gh options are gone, but all the cards are +$200 in price. So now, the next best to Elite thing, FTW3, goes for over $1000.So EVGA gave in to mining craze after all. I'm very disappointed. I'm not going to buy a video card for $1000+. You should have stayed loyal to your base, instead you simply threw them under the bus like everyone else. Now, all we can do is wait for manufacturers to find their senses. When this craze is over, I will not longer be your customer, that much I can guarantee you.

review_title: DO NOT BUY! Mic stopped working in less than 30 days & lights are useless.
review_body: They came to us in perfect condition at first.  The sound and Mic also worked great at first, but in order for the lights to work you have to plug the usb cord into a usb port. In order to do that you can't move around at all because the usb cord is extremely short, so you have to stay right next to where they're plugged in. So our son decided it wasn't worth it, therefore the lights are never on. Uggghh... But the worst part is, after less than a month, the mic no longer works at all! And our son takes VERY good care of his headset. So there's no way any damage came to them in our side. They look perfectly fine but without the mic working, there's no use for this headset. Our sons use headsets to play on their XBOX ONE Live Gold so it's no fun if no one can heard you. Do not buy these! Our other son has a different brand of headset that was even cheaper than these and it's been going strong for over 6 months. And he's 14 & not as careful as or 11 year old, but his headset had held up fine, even after our German Shepherd got a hold of them and chewed the mic a bit. So if that other brand can withstand our dog, and these ones stop working for no reason, then I STRONGLY suggest you buy a different brand. DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY ON THESE! No wonder they offer a protection plan. Instead of wasting my time calling to get a REFURBISHED pair of this garbage headset that will probably take 6-8 weeks to receive, I'm opting for buying a new, different brand of headset. Why use my protection plan for a used pair that doesn't light up and will most likely malfunction quickly and I'll be doing the same thing all over again. Uggghhh!ðŸ˜§ The pics show how the looked first day but how we had to use a cell phone charger to plug the usb in to make the lights work. The split cord is so short & no kid wants to sit in one place while playing Xbox. Our son was really disappointed because he thought the lights were so cool.

product_name: TCL 32S305 32-Inch 720p Roku Smart LED TV (2017 Model)
review_title: A Great Purchase/Great Value for the Money
review_body: *** I did not buy this TV from Amazon, I purchased it directly from Target for the same advertised price of $229.00**I wanted to really comment on this TV.  Setup is fantastic and quick.  It very quickly connected to my Wi-Fi and the Roku setup process was seamless.  I was able to create a Roku account and sign into the apps I already pay for (Netflix, Hulu Plus, Amazon Prime, CBS AA, Sling) and it's up and running.  My only complaint so far is the fact that there is no Ethernet port.  The TV connects to my Internet connection via Wi-Fi, which is great but that does not guarantee a consistent 1080p connection through Wi-Fi.  I will be purchasing a USB/Ethernet connection to plug directly into my modem.The remote is small but functional, I don't see a need for a big remote with a lot of buttons when the TV itself has a fantastic menu.I haven't yet connected any other devices, although there are plenty of connections.  This TV has 3 HDMI ports, a USB port, analog and digital input, and a digital TV tuner.  I'll update my review if necessary.

review_title: Better wifi and antenna reception that some other t.v.s, , more connections
review_body: I was looking for a small kitchen smart t.v. I bought this LG 24" smart t.v.,- https://smile.amazon.com/dp/B01LXHXGZX/ -  and had problems with reception from my antenna (broken and pixelated on a clear, clouless day - other t.v.s in the house w/similar connection had no issues), and with connecting to my wifi network. Returned it, wondering if it was just my sub-standard rural internet connection (which is admittedly not great), and went for this Samsung 24" smart t.v.. I have other Samsungs that have worked well, and thought it might be worth the extra money. The LG was white, which was nice in my setting, had more convenient remote features than the Samsung. However. the Samsung did connect with my wifi (the LG would find the network, connect, then refuse to load any wifi content), and has better reception of the signal from my antenna. If I lived in town with great wifi, the LG might have been more attractive, but in my rural setting, the Samsung came through with good reception, and a connection that will show streaming content (tried Amazon Prime video). I looked at a Vizio 1080 res, but it was short on connections. I wanted the potential to connect a DVD player in case I swap t.v. locations at a later date. The Samsung had 2 HDMI ports, and audio and video in. Other people complained about this t.v. dropping wifi connection. Will have to see how that goes. It's wonderful that it connects at all in my situation.

product_name: Sony KDL32W600D 32-Inch HD Smart TV (2016 Model)
review_title: So far, a fairly decent TV, but not so great for PC video. Shipping should've been in descrete package.
review_body: I was hoping to connect my PC to this TV, but it has no VGA port, unfortunately.Just has two HDMI ports. One of the ports, the ARC one, just happens to be where the vesa wall mount plate goes, and gets blocked by it.There is no VGA port, so you'll need a VGA to HDMI adapter to get an older PC's video to be picked up by the TV.I was disappointed to discover the set won't accept 1280x720, or 1920x720p from a PC.Supported Computer Resolutions:1024 x 768 (XGA), 1280 x 768 (WXGA), 1360 x 768, 640 x 480 (VGA), 800 x 600 (SVGA)There is also no way to connect PC audio directly to the set. That's handled by HDMI.The picture looks fairly even, all across the screen, in terms of brightness.Viewing angle is fairly decent. It is LCD, so, yeh, if you view from too acute an angle, the picture will look a bit dimmer. However, the brightness at acute viewing angles (greater than 45 degrees from center) is much better than most LCD sets I've had.Even high, and low position viewing looks decent.I did notice a wee bit of dimness in the far corners of the screen, but it's tolerable.It aint a CRT. LOL ;)Most LCDs I've had got washed out picture when viewed from very close. This one looks fairly decent, even at close distances.Audio is "ok", could be better, if the speakers were forward firing, instead of pointing at the floor. LOL.The set is very light weight, and perfect for mounting on a DJ lighting stand, with the proper vesa plate, and o-clamp attached.It'll be interesting to see how many years this one lasts. The last set I had only ran for 4 years, minimal usage per day, and was not a Sony.Would've been nice, had the set come with mounting screws for the vesa plate, though.The stand leaves a bit to be desired. It felt a bit flimsy, but then the set is very light weight.Would also have been nice if the set came with a coax, and HDMI cables. But then, most factories don't give you your money's worth anymore, anyway. LOL.I was not happy about the seller cheaping out on the shipping. I don't appreciate my purchases being shipped in retail containers. They're not meant for shipping, and don't hold up well to that. It also makes the product vulnerable to porch piracy, and dishonest delivery drivers.I'll update as needed.

First of all the picture quality is awesome and I am satisfied with it. It has minor problems with zoom and filling in the screen. My complaint is the fact that they have the nerve to claim this to be a smart TV. The apps available is very, very limited. If you only live on Netflix, Amazon and Hulu then perhaps you are good. But this TV has no business claiming a smart TV because it doesn't even have a standard browser. Under tools you can find a URL loader but once you are on a website what do you do? The remote affords no navigation or mouse function at all (unlike the pointer of the LG Smart TV). So it is impossible to use HBO GO app, Showtime, etc. The "Opera TV" does not come close to an app store.

Every couple days, an app will crash, and you have to restart it. Every few days, the wireless will stop connecting even though every other device in my house works just fine in the same room. The wireless will not connect again until I turn the TV off and back on. Lately, it has been forgetting the wireless password all-together, so I'm forced to retype it in a long string of letters and numbers. The remote control is also pretty terrible. Pressing buttons sometimes works, sometimes doesn't. The keyboard on the back is even worse. It looks neat, but fails to register about 1 in 5 button presses. If I wasn't already past the 90-day warranty, I would return it.

review_title: Best wireless headphones I've had in a while in this price range
review_body: These are really good headphones especially if you have an up-to-date phone. They are already loud and pretty clear but Smartthings automatically adjust it to your music based on your preferences. The wire-clamp is useless but luckily the wire isn't overly long like some other bluetooth headphones i have had. Changing to the smaller tips they fit perfectly in my ear and there isn't that constant cutting out when i jog. Battery also last pretty long on a charge.I do find it weird that the button in the front when these are on your ears is the button to go to the previous track and the button behind is to go forward, weird choice.If you don't adjust your settings for the buds they will sound very basic i tested them on two phones all week both up-to-date cells and noticed a huge difference. Also be careful with bluetooth 4.0 disconnect from devices you don't want to use if you don't want them switching between devices.In the end anything i was not satisfied with these are completely outweighed by the fact at how inexpensive they are.

product_name: Microsoft Surface Pro (Intel Core i5, 8GB RAM, 256GB) - Newest Version
review_title: Perfect tablet? or Perfect laptop? Who knows?
review_body: I have the SP4 and I got it at Best Buy bc I don't think buying an item like this on Amazon because you never know when the seller bought the tablet and if you purchased this from Amazon and they purchased this a 6 months ago, you're sol, you'll only have 6 month warranty left on the tablet/laptop. I bought this from Best Buy and the keyboard separately. I also bought the accidental coverage in case I were to drop it and break it within the first year. It was worth it because I could accidentally drop it while putting it in my backpack and I would get a replacement for free.I am typically an Apple fanboy but the 12.9" iPad Pro did not cut it for the type of work that I do. I bought the 12.9" iPad Pro for my wife because that's just what she wanted and I could not access my work programs using anything other than IE11 and only Windows uses IE11. Plus, my MB Pro is about 6yrs old and I wanted something that was lighter and a little more portable and updated. Thus the SP4 was purchased. I bought the i5/4GB/128GB version. I wasn't too worries about the speed since the programs I'm using is cloud based minus Adobe but some of the documents are stored in the cloud too. The SP4 just offered me more of what I needed. I miss the Apple integration but I'm gaining a lot more features that I can use for WORK. Now I can work from home and my boss would have no problems with it. I mean, before the SP4 I was using the iPad Mini 4 to track my loans and take notes on it but size really matters. Plus, I can't use my work system on any Apple devices so I had no choice. It was either that or I go into the office everyday rather than going straight to my laptop. I'm on salary anyways so it doesn't mean I have to work 40hrs/week even though I do because I'm not lazy.This is the perfect solution for someone who wants the tablet but also have it function like a laptop. There are too many things that you can't do on an Apple computer than on a Windows device. I will always be an Apple fanboy but for work I need this laptop. I know it's really a tablet but it's a laptop to me because I use it like a laptop and like a laptop it has an USB port, Thunderport, Miscro SD card slot and it also offers you 1TB of cloud storage so having only 128GB of memory didn't bother me at all. Everything is in the cloud these days, I don't even use my USB drive anymore because I can store everything in the cloud and it follows me everywhere I go. I would suggest that you get a full keyboard for this tablet so that you don't lose about half your screen space plus it's a lot easier to type on a keyboard rather than the on screen keyboard. Yes, it costs more but it depends on what you want to do with it. If you want a laptop style tablet and you want all the functionality of a laptop then you will need the keyboard. Plus, it acts like a case and keeps your screen from fingerprints and scratches. Do yourself a favor and get the keyboard. If you don't think you'll need the keyboard then buy an iPad Pro or just an iPad.You won't regret purchasing the keyboard with the tablet. It will be used and it will come in handy, granted it drains your battery but again, it comes down to what you're using the tablet for. Plus you'll like the fact there is a trackpad instead of using your fingers on the screen.

product_name: Epiphone Les Paul SPECIAL-II Electric Guitar, Vintage Sunburst
review_title: Great for starters or something that you don't have to have an insurance policy on.
review_body: To start I bought this guitar on prime day, so I got it for like a hundred bucks. I've always played acoustic electric but wanted to try an electric as they have a much broader range of capabilities. I didn't want to spend a lot of money and saw this and knew that Epiphone was well enough worth the price. This thing is impressive, pickups are hopped up for even the $200 regular price. After playing this and hearing it, 200 is still very reasonable. If you are looking for a good starter or something you don't have to worry about watching your every move around that can take some dings and scratches, this is a great option. Nice finish, sounds great, and won't break the bank. Is it a Les Paul?, not at all, it is also not a grand. But it is a great guitar to learn on and see if you enjoy it enough to spend more money on something nicer. I will say however, for the price range, I honestly don't think there is a better deal for a new guitar with a brand most everyone has heard of.

product_name: Yamaha Pacifica Series PAC112J Electric Guitar; Black
review_title: One of the best guitars for $500 or less
review_body: I picked this one up a couple of years ago. I'm not in a band, I'm not an expert guitarist... I'm just an intermediate-level player, so take what I say with a grain of salt. But this is the best guitar I've tried for $500 or less. I love the coil split on the tuning knob that turns the humbucker bridge pickup into effectively a single-coil (like a strat). It has 22 frets, nicer for a few solos. :)  The tremolo bar (bah, I'm from the 80s, I call it a whammy bar) is fairly standard low-end... nothing great...  EXCEPT be warned that it has an unusual threading on the arm itself, so it may be hard to find a replacement short of contacting Yamaha themselves. I mostly keep mine in storage and rarely use it. For the most part, it's quality construction, easy to hold and play, reasonably lightweight, and holds its tuning well. It's held up great for two years, so it's been perfect for me.

product_name: Yamaha Pacifica Series PAC112J Electric Guitar; Black
review_body: I've owned a lot of guitars over the 45 years I've been playing and this is one of the best, beating out quite a few I paid a lot more for. Fit and finish can't be faulted, and it plays and sounds great. I've owned several Yamaha instruments and they've all been excellent. As mentioned in other reviews, the packaging was atrocious. It comes in the basic cardboard box you see in guitar stores with no padding or reinforcement inside the box. Only two strips of packing tape hold the box closed. It was obvious someone had tried to lift the box by the lid flap because it was torn wide open and you could see the guitar without opening the box. Fortunately there was no damage, but the packaging definitely needs improvement.

review_title: there is some fret buzz and it could use a good setup by a qualified luthier but then so could ...
review_body: For the price you pay for this instrument, it's a bargain.  It is, for all intents and purposes, a Fender Stratocaster clone without the name and accompanying price tag.  And because it's a Yamaha - one of the premier musical instrument manufacturers in the world - you can be assured it's not junk.

product_name: Yamaha Pacifica Series PAC112J Electric Guitar; Black
review_title: The Pacifica 112V is better than most
review_body: I've played other brand guitars of my friends in this price range. The Pacifica 112V is better than most, but it isn't the best value. You might find a guitar you like better by shopping at your local guitar stores. Take time visiting all of the local music stores before you make your choice.

product_name: Yamaha Pacifica Series PAC112J Electric Guitar; Black
review_body: I might be inclined to give this instrument 3 1/2 stars if that were allowed, but rounding up is probably more fair than rounding down, so I give it 4. It delivers a lot of value, in that it sounds great, and the parts that matter most are solidly crafted. By that I mean the neck and body - this guitar is made out of nice wood, and looks terrific. I can't really judge the quality of the tuning machine or the bridge, since this is the first instrument I've owned, but I was disappointed by the electronics, which seem to me to be dirt cheap. A few week after buying it I started getting horribly painful buzzing and popping sounds every time my body shifted, and when I took the backplate off to inspect the innards, discovered that the output jack was very poorly soldered. I took the extra step of removing the old solder so I could redo it competently. The jack itself is very cheap and flimsy, and I will probably try to replace it with something better at some point. Upon inspecting the rest of the electronic, I'm rather motivated to replace all of them in the coming years, or else buy a higher quality guitar. So I guess my final verdict is, it's a great instrument for beginners on a tight budget, but you get what you pay for. It will look and sound good for the time being, but you may want to brush up on your soldering skills before buying.

product_name: Yamaha Pacifica Series PAC112J Electric Guitar; Black
review_body: Better than any Squier, hands-down. However, I do recommend to anyone serious about playing a Strat to look into a Fender MIM. This is the closest you'll get to a pro-level guitar, and at a fair price. I went through the same motions as many, thinking "Can I get by on a decent guitar priced under 300"? Well, I've been a musician my whole life, primarily a saxophone player. The sound is where it's at, period. Second, build quality - how it feels in your hands. Compared to a real Fender, this Pacifica and 'all' Squiers feel like a toy. Sound wise, the Yamaha will do ... but add about 100-200 bucks onto your spending budget and get yourself a Fender, used or new, just make sure it's in good shape and setup correctly. These cheap guitars will hold you back. I am still learning to play guitar, and was shocked at how much better I sound on a Fender MIM. Best of all, I just can't put it down!

product_name: Dean EVO XM Solid Body Electric Guitar - Satin Natural
review_title: Only my first guitar, but I absolutely love it.
review_body: Being from Tampa, I wanted my first guitar to be a Dean. Sure, there are plenty of other options out there, but I just had it in my head thats what I wanted. Well, I must say I am very happy with the purchase. Guitar arrived in its triangular shelf box, inside another Dean shipping box, which was wrapped in bubble sheet packed inside yet another, larger, Amazon box. Was essentially ready to play right out of the box, with a few quick turns of the tuning pegs. One knock on it I have seen online before buying was that the tuners don't hold tight, I have not yet had this problem after a week of playing it, including some drastic bends. Checked with a steel straightedge and a light, the neck was dead flat and straight. The edges of the frets could use some more finishing, they are still a bit edgy. I have seen others mention filing them down a bit, same thing that would be done on a more expensive guitar at the factory. I will probably get some diamond files and do this as well, I keep hanging up my hand on them on the bottom of the neck. I'm no expert on tone, but this has a nice even sound and responds well to pretty much any pedals or effects I've thrown at it. I did restring mine with the DR Neon Multi-Color strings for using with Rocksmith, which required adjusting the intonation. The low E and A strings ended up at the very end of their range, and the A is actually still a tiny bit flat. This could well be a factor of those particular strings though, so I wont knock the guitar for it. As others have noted, the finish can vary drastically. Mine is much darker than the stock photo and the grain is much less noticeable. Overall, looks a nice piece, especially for the cost. I could not ask for better for this price. From what I hear from more experienced players, as I progress I could easily upgrade the tuners and pickups, though I think I will leave this one alone and just get a higher end guitar when its time.

product_name: Dean EVO XM Solid Body Electric Guitar - Satin Natural
review_body: Almost 3 years ago i bought this guitar to start off my guitar players journey. Did I expect to stick with it? No, but thankfully I did, and I would encourage any aspiring musicians to do the same. After all, the first month is the hardest. Did this instrument attribute to me deciding to stick with guitar? Honestly I think so, I was a beginner back then and I did not know much about quality vs price in these instruments so I picked my favorite looking guitar I could find in my price range. It doesn't sound great, it doesn't stay in tune, and it doesn't feel great to play. But for this price can I really complain? I don't think so. For me what kept me coming back was looking at its Les Paul style design and visioning myself playing along with Slash or Page on the big stages with a full blown Gibson. This leads me to my main point which is at this price range whatever you get will suck so i suggest you buy a guitar based on the type of guitar you hope to one day play. If you dont know what you want to play think of your favorite artists, Pink Floyd fans for instance will want to go for a Squier Strat and Guns N' Roses fans like myself might find an Epiphone Les Paul most enjoyable. Now that Iv rambled on for a few minutes and havent really gotten anywhere I'll just leave you with one more bit of advice. If your certain you cant spend any more than $200 on a guitar go for the big companies like Fender (Fenders Squier range) and Epiphone, and go for the guitar that you think will get you picking up the guitar again, because at the end of the day it doesn't matter how good your guitar sounds and feels if you just don't like it.

product_name: Jackson JS22 Dinky - Metallic Blue
review_title: Incredible guitar with some slight adjustments.
review_body: So I was skeptical about this guitar, 200 bucks is pretty cheap. I promise this is worth every penny and more...with a little work. I've been playing guitar, specifically for metal, for 19 years and have had owned over 20 guitars in my lifetime. I've had other Jacksons, Ibanez, B.C. Rich, Schecter, Fender, Epiphone, Gibson, and more. This is every bit as good as the $1000+ plus guitars I have owned in every way. Here's what you can do out of the box to make this a throat slashing metal machine. First off, TIGHTEN THE TUNING MACHINES! They were definitely loose on mine and the guitar was coming out of tune very quickly. After tightening them, the guitar stays in tune for weeks at a time. There was some minor fret buzz on the high E, I found the fret giving me trouble, I used a luthiers file and ever so slightly trimmed the height of the fret bar. Problem solved. The action right out of the box was perfect for me, I like it close. I know have an excellent guitar that I could not be happier with. If you want the Floyd Rose, pay the extra $100 and get the same model with that. I personally despise the Floyd Rose, so this model is for me. I find that the pickups are pretty hot and I  didn't need to replace them.

product_name: Premium Weighted Blanket, Perfect Size and Weight (12lb) For Adults...
review_body: I purchased this blanket a couple of weeks ago.  I must say, this is the best blanket I've ever purchased for my bed!  I purchased the gray only because I have a feeling my kids might want to take it on me!!!  If they do - I'll definitely be buying another.  I was apprehensive at first because I didn't understand how a blanket could calm people.  Well - my mistake.  I guess they're out there!  I do not sleep well at all.  I toss and turn most of the night.  God forbid I get up to go to the bathroom, I'm up for at least an hour before I can fall back asleep again.  Although not diagnosed, I know I have anxiety issues and the possibility of depression.  Thoughts go through my head about anything and everything.  Sometimes I find myself even making up stories in my head.  I just cannot turn the thoughts off when I go to bed.  It drives me absolutely nuts because I am so tired when I wake up.  I figured, what the heck - I'll try this blanket out.First off, I don't understand why people complain and give it less marks because it's warm.  Of course it's warm!!!  It's a weighted 12lb blanket - what do people expect?  Where less to bed or get a fan, buy it's no excuse to take marks off.  I am starting to suffer from hot flashes and quite honestly, although I still get them at night, not as much with this blanket.  Maybe my other comforter is made of another material that doesn't breathe as good, I don't know.  I was afraid to try this blanket because of my hot flashes but I just didn't care anymore, I wanted to try something.This blanket is so soft!!  The 12lb weight is perfect and I'm sure if it was heavier, it would be fine for me.  I can always just fold it in 1/2 for double the weight but I have not done that yet.  I have a king size bed so it does not fit.  But I don't care.  It would definitely fit a full and possibly a queen, but not a king.  Again - I don't care.  The first night I used this blanket I slept like a baby.  Then the next night - same thing.  Granted, this blanket is not a miracle blanket.....I still have thoughts going in my head at night, but no where near as much.  If I get up to go to the bathroom - I fall back asleep probably in about 10/15 minutes or so.  Much better than before.  We went away for a few nights.  Again - here come all of those thoughts again racing through my head....what we did that day, plans for the next day, what I should've done, what's the weather going to be like, etc.  Came home exhausted from little sleep.  Went to bed with my new blanket - fell asleep pretty quick and got much needed sleep.  That proved to me that this blanket does help people with anxiety issues.  Again - it's no miracle worker - but for me personally - it really helps out a lot.  If they weren't so expensive, I'd probably buy a few more but for the time being - this blanket is all mine - that is....until my kids find out about it!  lolOh....and yes - there are ties inside to keep everything in place.  There is a tie in all 4 corners and a tie in the middle.  There's supposed to be a loop on both sides but mine was missing one.  So, instead of having 8 loops/ties....mine has 8 ties with only 7 loops.  The zipper is approximately 15" long.  I did not measure.  Blanket is super soft - solid on one side and texture on the other side.  I have not tried washing it yet so I cannot comment on that.If one can afford it, I would highly suggest giving this blanket a try if you suffer from anxiety issues.  If it can calm someone like myself, I'm sure it can work wonders for other people!!!!

First and foremost, the quality of the blanket is great. The feel and texture are amazing, so cuddly and soft and keeps you incredibly warm ( yea I know I said it was for my son but of course I had to try it out). My son for the first time in forever (it seems) sleep in his own bed, all through the night...it's amazing.Only thing, as much as I love the outter covering of the blanket (the soft fuzzy velour), I do wonder how it will be in the summer - I may have to get a lighter cover. Other than that, the weight and size is perfect. SO glad I made the purchase.

review_body: This blanket is very comfortable and comes with a removable cover that is soft and protects the weighted blanket.  I got a 20lb banket as I am 190lbs.  It is comfortable, seems well made (no indication of any rips or tears/filling leaking) and is as advertised on length.  Its not a whole bed size and is more for an individual.  The way the internal weighted blanket is made, it doesn't seem to suffer from shifting of the weight (piling up in one side or another).  The weight is sown into individual chambers to prevent this.  Only "issues" I have had is it can be a little warm and the way it is attached to the cover (tied to the four corners) it can "bunch" some inside.  This is rather simply resolved by repositioning it.  Overall, I am very satisfied.

review_body: I have always wanted to try this, but I was a bit nervous by the price tag. Lucky for me, I was able to get one at a discount in return for my honest review. I got the 15lb Navy version. The outer cover is very soft, which is one of my requirements in blankets. I wouldn't say it was navy; it was more of an indicolyte or muted royal-blue. Very nice color. The weighted part has little loops that you can tie the cover into. I was surprised how heavy it felt to maneuver.I wanted to do a good test, so I decided to lounge with it on the couch. I noticed how cozy and warm it was. This was great because it is still cold here. It might be too hot in the summer if there is not strong AC. I was also surprised how quickly I "settled down" and felt like I wanted to nap. I think this is going to be my go-to napping blanket. It just felt really good. I probably won't sleep with it at night because I sleep hot. All-in-all, I'm very happy with this purchase and am thinking of buying the smallest weight to help my dog when there are storms.

Needing a pair fast, so as not to endure a cross-country trip without music, I searched Amazon for a cheap pair that offered same day delivery. I found these headphones listed for under $20, and figured they'd get me through the journey satisfactorily. I am beyond thrilled to report that these far exceeded my expectations. I lack the writing skills to adequately convey just how great these headphones are, so all I'll say is that anyone who purchases this product will not be disappointed in the least.

review_title: Great Audiophile Headphones for the price
review_body: I went through several sets of wireless headphones to find the best high fidelity quality sound and comfort for the money before settling on the Sennheiser HD 4.50's. I'm a huge Bowers & Wilkins fan as an owner of their speakers so I started with the P5 wireless and while sounding great they didn't fit my head well and I could hear outside sounds fairly easy, I liked the sound but the fit was a no go. Then I decided to step up to the P7 wireless which fit fantatic and are just a beautiful headphone. My issue with the P7 wireless was the base was just to heavy and on some tracks overpowered the mids and vocals which didn't fit my taste. I was disappointed because I really loved the feel and fit of them and they are a beautiful headphone but unfortunately it was  0 - 2 for Bowers & Wilkins headphones.

product_name: Sennheiser HD 4.50 Bluetooth Wireless Headphones with Active Noise...
review_body: Quality

product_name: Sennheiser HD 4.50 Bluetooth Wireless Headphones with Active Noise...
review_body: So as a whole the headphones are really nice.  Comfortable to a point, as with all headphones that I use after so long my ears/head just can't take it anymore.  I'm perfectly satisfied that this could be an issue with my big a** head.  With that said they are still very comfortable, very cushiony actually. These are probably the easiest headphones to pair up, with past headphones pairing mode always had to be activated outside of turning the power on. There is no pairing mode for these, you turn it on and if it doesn't connect to anything it activates pairing mode, it's as seamless as you could want.  Though, the next easiest way is by NFC, which is installed in the left earcup, just turn on NFC on your phone, touch the ear cup and it connects.  About as easy as it gets, couldn't have asked for a better way to pair devices.  The noise cancelling works pretty darn good, it's not perfect, there's been a couple of static frequencies that it couldn't drown out but i only noticed it when i either paused the music or in between songs.  Now that I've talked about the good things i'll touch on the bad ones. I can only find a few of them which is a good thing in my mind.  So i know a different review touched on this aspect so I think I should as well, just to show some continuity on the matter.  So the company says these are over the ear headphones, that's a bit of a technicality.  They technically are over the ear, but the area that's supposed to go around the ear isn't very big so unless you have small ears part of the cushion will be resting on your ears.  If you have big ears, sort of like myself, there is a way to, as you put them on, to fold your ears into the hole without it being uncomfortable.  Another negative is the headphone cord, now it's not necessarily the cord, the jack that's on the earcup isn't the best design so you can easily not plug it in all the way.  Though you will know when you don't because, while the sound comes in on both speakers, it sounds like you've hit the "concert hall" theme on the equalizer so it's very echoey.  Once you plug it in correctly it's hard to tell the difference in sound between the headphone jack and the bluetooth.  The last negative is the "multi-function" button on the earcup, it's got more functionality than most headphones, though half of those functions will only work with their proprietary music player.  Only the general functions will work across devices.The proprietary player is really nice looking i just wish it would be able to interact with other source audios.  As an example itunes or google music, i already pay a subscription fee for music I'm not going to cancel one that works very well for a different one that only works really well with one set of headphones.

review_body: I ordered these for my husband for Christmas. They are replacing a pair of Sony earphones that he's had for over 15 years. They have a long cord and it has just become a big jumbled mess.

review_body: These look really nice, with a leather like strap across the top. These connected to both my phone and my professional grid beat maker without a problem. The sound is great with a bumping bass.

review_title: Excellent headphones for much less than the big names.
review_body: My teenage son is not swayed by expensive name brand items when their are other options for a fraction of the price. He is very impressed with these Panasonic headphones. They are comfortable for him to wear over the ears for an extended period of time for music and gaming. They were easy to pair have have a nice long battery life for hours and hours of listening enjoyment.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: Sound is great, connectivity is reliable. Can't complain at all. I love the vintage look but the sound is far from vintage it is state of the art today.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: This is my first set of bluetooth headphones so I am certainly no expert.  First, let me say they were easy to pair with my Kindle.  I got these to use at home, but I wouldn't like them if I needed to travel with them since they do not fold.  I think the sound is good, although not exceptional.  I don't think these are considered noise cancelling headphones, which my regular headphones are.  I do prefer the noise cancelling feature in headphones although it may cost a little more.  I have several Panasonic products and have always found them to be reliable products.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: These are long lasting bluetooth headphones that last about as long as they promise. They are comfortable enough to wear during a TV binging session, but probably not ideal in terms of comfort if you plan to wear them all day every day. They connect and reconnect to Android and Windows 10 without problems. Charging is simple, using the included charging cable, they take about as much time as the manual says. I typically charge them overnight or when I'm not planning to use them for a while.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: These headphones sound really good. I used them to listen to music and podcasts on my phone, via Bluetooth, and the sound quality was excellent. I'm not a connoisseur, but I thought the low and high ends were strong. In appearance, these headphones look like the ones we used in the language lab back in high school -- these are no fancy Beats, which is fine with me.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: I love the retro styling on these and they sound incredible. Full spectrum, rock solid Bluetooth connection. They have a good "feel" - not too light, not too heavy. Comfortable enough to wear for a few hours. Can't go wrong at this price either.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: Comfortable Wireless Headphones With Good Sound Quality
review_body: These Panasonic headphones yield a good, balanced sound quality.  They are also lightweight, extremely comfortable and easy to adjust to different head sizes, thanks to a simple design that allows you to adjust the width by sliding the earphones along a metal track.  The Bluetooth technology works well, and they are easy to charge and connect.  The headphones have an attractive retro look about them, though this might not be a selling point for the younger generation, which seems to crave black headphones.  They also don't have the noise canceling quality of other headphones, and the sound is audible by those nearby at higher volumes.  If you're looking for a comfortable and serviceable set of over-the-ear headphones, however, this Panasonic product offers a good value for your money.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: Great Bluetooth headphones -- but tiny control buttons
review_body: These are very comfortable headphones that  sound great (no static, clear sound, and good noise-cancelling).  The Bluetooth is easy to connect to a phone or iPod, and they're easy to charge.  I like the look of them, and they easily adjust to fit my husband as well as they fit me.  They're light-weight and cool-looking -- I like the retro look without all the wires.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: The retro look is interesting, but ultimately this fall a little bit flat, like the sound.  From a distance they look good, but up close they can appear to be a bit light on the detail (read â€œCheap.â€�). Indeed they are very light which can be a positive or negative depending on how you look at it.  Not easy to travel with as they do NOT fold up nor do they come with a case.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: The best bluetooth headphones I've heard, and the only ones I've liked enough to actually use. I tested the sound against another "retro" styled headphone, the Grado Labs SR 80e studio headphones. For sure, the Panasonics don't have the same clarity in the high end and low end, but all the sound samples I listened to were pleasing, and I could hear all the instruments: in jazz, drum and bass, and speaking / interview. So, decent sound quality, even if it were wired. But wireless, it's awesome. It's the fourth Bluetooth set I've tried, and it's the only one that doesn't suck. :-)

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: Easy to use, surprisingly good audio quality
review_body: These headphones were extremely easy to get setup via both my Galaxy S8+ phone and my Windows 10 computer. They connect via bluetooth and in both cases I was able to get connected and start using them immediately (I've had varied success with other bluetooth devices). Once I got them connected I was pleasantly surprised that the audio quality was pretty darn good. I listened to some of my favorite songs via streaming and I got good quality across all levels. I also watched a couple of movies and was similarly impressed. Probably the only knock I have is the volume level is not all that loud which I could compensate a little bit with the volume on the phone laptop. This isn't a big deal to me because I don't like it to be ear bleeding loud anyway. Overall, very good headphones.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: They're Comfortable and Sound Great - Battery Life is Fantastic
review_body: For me, Bluetooth headphones are the greatest thing ever invented. I love being able to listen to music or audiobooks while I'm working without bothering anyone else. The problem has been one of comfort and, to some extent, durability. I'm on the move a lot so I need to be able to cram them into a backpack and be fairly certain they won't be damaged. These are my basic conditions.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: Comfortable, but sound is just ok
review_body: These are really comfortable headphones.  I have a big head and sometimes have trouble finding headphones that wrap comfortably.  These do with room to spare.  The cups are soft and the set is really lightweight, so high marks for comfort.  The sound is just acceptable though.  Not great.  Iâ€™ve had trouble with the connection momentarily dropping too.  It cuts out for half a second at least once every 10 minutes.  I have other Bluetooth headphones and earpieces and donâ€™t have trouble with those, so itâ€™s definitely this set.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: No issues, feel good, sound good.
review_body: Very comfortable speakers, and paired with my iPhone 7 in a snap. They did indeed fully charge in under 3 hours, and then played for a long time. Canâ€™t tell you if it would have been 24 hours continuous, because my days of all-nighters are over, but I can tell you that over the course of a week I played them for at least 12 hours off and on and they were fine. The charge held for 3 weeks easy.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: Pairing doesn't work on mine correctly.
review_body: I really really wanted to love these since it clearly states that they can be connected to multiple devices (all of mine are listed) and they are a really awesome retro look and cordless! The 24 hour battery life was a big eye opener as well. But sadly they just do not stand up to all that they say they do. I can only get them to connect to either my phone or my husbands - but you have to completely delete the saved bluetooth connection in order to get them to connect to another device. I have gone back and fourth with panasonic via phone and live chat about this and they just told me over and over to remove the connection on the phone to pair to another device. That makes no sense to me at all - why take the time to set up and pair the device to my phone so I can use them when I am doing whatever and then another day my husband wants to use them with his phone when working and I have to unpair it on my phone so he can pair with his phone.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_title: Comfortable, good battery life, good quality sound, easy!
review_body: These headphones are everything I'd want from wireless headphones: the sound is good, no static, they actually hold a charge, they're fairly comfortable and they're durable. They also look good and stay connected remarkably well. I've had no problem pairing them with all my devices (all of them Apple).

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: Very comfortable.  Excellent quality.  Bluetooth pairs up nicely with everything that i have tried.  Excellent range.  Can walk from the back of the house to the mailbox and lose nothing.  Excellent battery life.  Charges in less than three hours.

product_name: PANASONIC Wireless Retro Over-The-Ear Headphones with Bluetooth...
review_body: These are very good headphones. The sound quality is good and they are comfortable. I love that they are wireless. My only gripe is the "retro" look. The metal protrudes past the bottom of the headphone. This is not such a big problem for adults, but it makes for a weird fit when we use them for my toddler daughter.

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_title: Don't get carried away. One drop is all you need.
review_body: This is without a doubt the hottest sauce I have ever bought. One drop in a bowl of stew does the trick. It will make your eyes water and make you sweaty.  Just exact what I was looking for. This bottle will last a long time.

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_title: Tastes Like a Pile of Burning Tire-Rubber, but it's a Classic
review_body: When I was a kid, I have some seriously traumatic memories of this stuff ruining my day on a couple occasions. In fact until recently I only used this stuff as an additive to heat up other more flavorful sauces. Now that there are lots of sauces that are both several-times hotter and have much better flavor, I doubt I'll be revisiting this sauce any time soon. I'll give Dave's Original Insanity a tip of the hat for being a classic that really introduced me to the soul-searing heat of extract sauces. But in the current world with tons and tons of other options, do your research before settling for this sauce.

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: this hot sauce is great

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_title: I love spicy food but be careful with this
review_body: Incredibly hot. I love spicy food but be careful with this. Difficult to pour just a little from the bottle so don't pour directly onto your food or you may regret if too much comes out of the bottle.  A couple drops is all you need. I'll let my son have this one. Too much and it is painful all the way through, if you know what I mean.  This is military grade hot sauce.

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: Smack you in your mouth hot it's for CHILI HEADS, NOT YOUR EVERYDAY PEOPLE.if you don't enjoy the kick , burn,hot flashes the sweats,the pure joy of waking up your taste buds this is NOT for you! Stick to the vinegar grocery store Frank's /Louisanna hot sauce and all the other mass production of BITTER excuse for hot sauce

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: This is pretty hot, but the extract in it tastes like a well behaved pepperspray or O.C. As we call it in the law enforcement community. I have been pepper sprayed as part of my police training and found that this sauce has a very similar flavor to that Sabre Red. Its like a strong dried red cayenne pepper flavor. To conclude, i will say that this sauce is not for a beginner or average consumer, i call it "medium" heat, but I'm a chili head and like that kind of pain.

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_title: Exactly what it says on the package - Insanity
review_body: Extremely hot! This sauce is no joke. My dad tried a spoonful of it while he was working up in Alaska. Big mistake. He couldn't breathe. It nearly sent him to the hospital. I was smart enough to put some on a spoon and then dip the tip of my tongue into it, not try and eat a whole spoonful. This sauce is extremely thick and concentrated. It barely runs out of the bottle without some shaking for encouragement. It has a very bitter pepper extract flavor up-front, with a touch of smoky habanero. If you can get over the nasty bitterness, you might even be encouraged to try some more. Don't. Then, the burn hits. After tasting just a little of this, you will need milk. Like, five glasses of milk. And it's oily and the milk just spreads it around your mouth and makes the burn worse, at first. If you like spicing up your food, this is very economical; a teaspoon will make any dish almost inedibly hot for most people. One bottle will last a very, very long time. Don't be dismayed by the gross flavor; when diluted in a bowl of chili con carne, the bitterness vanishes.

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: Great flavor and spice

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: love it

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: I love this stuff!! Daveâ€™s Insanity Sauce is delicious!!

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: hotttttttt, whew

product_name: Dave's Original Insanity Hot Sauce - 5oz
review_body: This stuff is definitely insane.  I am a big fan of hot sauces and occasionally I get some to where I'm feeling the heat, and it's almost uncomfortable.  Sometimes.  But I like that heat and I like it being a tad uncomfortable.But THIS stuff....Let me tell you a story.  My girlfriend bought me this, not knowing how hot it was.  I was pretty excited for a new hot sauce.  You know, whatever.  But I decided to take a quick break at work and pour some on a flour tortilla and try it out.So I put a nice LINE of it down...like a shoelace.  The equivalent to maybe 40 or 50 drops.MISTAKE!!!!!!!!!!The funny thing was that I got a very important conference call just a minute after this happened.I tried honey packets, water, clenching my fists, biting my fist, swearing to myself.So I would call it hot no problem.Aside from the heat, I think it tastes a little weird.I have had this for about eight months and the bottle is still 90% full.One drop at a time, people.
