review_body: I enjoyed this album when it came out in the early seventies. He had some great music fronting the Animals. I've heard a lot of music since then. Hearing this recording again after four decades, I'm impressed by the power of Burdon's delivery.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_body: Excellent! If you like blues, and individualistic interpretations of covers - AND - if you always loved Eric Burdon 'back in the day' - you will, simply, LOVE this!  ;-)

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_body: Eric Burdon is so off key in some of the songs, note NIghts in White Satin II, that it actually hurts the ears.  When you listen to the samples, there isn't enough to hear how bad it is.  How could anyone allow such horrible recordings to be put on a CD is beyond me.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_body: This is one of the greatest albums ever recorded. Eric Burdon left the San Fran Animals in 1969 and wanted a diverse collection of jazz and funk musicians to swing with, what he found was the band War and they recorded Eric Burdon Declares in '69. That one has stayed in the memories of the public, sort of, with tracks appearing on Animals Best of packages and so forth, but for some reason THIS, the bands second album BLACK MANS BURDON is somewhat lost in the cracks, which is nothing less than a shame, given how amazingly it comes off once you spin it.Basically I dig The Animals and Eric Burdon a ton, which in its phases was both heavy duty real ace bar rock and roll and then some weirdo flower power stuff that hasnt translated so great overt time. WAR brought the life back to Eric Burdons sound, with a full large funky groove. You got horns, flutes, keys, and a whole array of percussions, groovy ladies in the background, and then Eric Burdon. Perhaps you know Spill the Wine or Tobacco Road from 'Declares'... those are great, but I would have to say that while that first album does its best at testing the water, what you find on this, is them fully understanding the water and then parting the sea.As a two disc vinyl I appreciate each side, for having its own groove. Side one represents the Paint it Black Medley, Side Two is a homage to Nights in White Satin... these songs are not traditional covers, they break them apart and experiment wildly with them, given that these songs were probably never in the repetoire of War before Eric Burdon, the band does everything to make it their own...and succeed!!!  The other sides have their own things happening as well. As a LP enthusiast I deeply like double LPS where every side counts, it does with Black Mans Burdon.  Trust me, the entire hour and a half is fully engaging and wild, I think this may be the best thing to ever come out of Eric Burdon or War, and I really like most of the other stuff.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_title: Eric's Best Album and War's beginning to fame
review_body: This is my favourite album by Eric Burdon. to me even better than his time with the Animals. War is the perfect backup band for Eric, but they are even better Solo see the World is a ghetto. However this is a great album on its own. The version of Paint It Black may be better than the Stones version. Eric really moved away from the limitations of the Animals and War's excellent muscianship gives him great freedom to explore.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_title: I really like it; but it's probably not for everyone
review_body: This is a tough album to review. I really like it; but it's probably not for everyone.  Recorded / released in 1970, this album reflects some of the musical trends that were prevalent at the time: Blues, Rock, Jazz, Latin, Psychedelic...  There are others, Santana to name one, that married these influences to greater success; but this album deserves a listen if only for the quality of the musicianship.  Eric Burdon is an excellent vocalist; but it's really WAR that carries the weight here.  Eric Burdon was still in a Trippy Psychedelic phase during this time - probably a little out of sync with the direction of WAR - so you get an interesting hybrid.  This album might have the greatest appeal to fans of the early 70's music, where there we so many musical styles being explored / merged.  In the context of the period, this is an interesting and mostly enjoyable album.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_body: Excellent product and service.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_title: another great meeting of Eric and a group called War
review_body: This the follow up of the classic first album of Eric and the band War helping to take Eric's music into the 70's. There is a lot of music here to love. They really take their time to explore the music with the opening track of Paint It Black which is a 13+ minutes of a journey. A great meeting of the music of War and of Eric who you will remember his wonderful 60's group the Animals which broke up towards the later days of the 60's. Side one opens with Paint It Black and finishes with them taking Nights In White Satin through some changes.The second cd continues with the nice blend of blues, rock and soul.

product_name: The Black-Man's Burdon
review_body: Assuming you already know the music (if not, check it out on Youtube), here's some info about the latest CD edition of this sprawling opus (and yes, I like the sprawl).The record company obviously thought that what we wanted was a bare-bones issue without a booklet; the front inlay is just a slip of paper with the front picture on one side and some minimal credits on the other. There's no list of musicians, just composers' credits, which interestingly omit Eric Burdon completely (erroneously or deliberately, I wonder?).I don't understand why anyone would want to buy such an incomplete package. If you're only interested in the music, a download will do. If you want the album with all the elements that historically should be part of it, this version leaves a lot to be desired.PS: I can't help wondering if the picture that adorned the inside of the original gatefold was omitted on purpose, since it really is in dubious taste. Back in the day, Robert Christgau's scathing review of the album solely consisted of a description of the album cover, with particular emphasis on that picture.PPS: As far as I can make out, the CD's have not been re-mastered, but the original mastering sounds acceptable to me - not great, but pretty close to the sound of the vinyl, which wasn't perfect to begin with.

product_name: Europe '72 [Live]
review_body: This album is a classic and a must-have for Deadheads and Touchheads alike. Every song is fantastic. This was their first tour with Keith Godchaux and their last with Ronald Charles McKernan, so there's an interesting transition taking place. Hurts Me Too with Pigpen on vocals is the last blues song they would do until the late 80s, and he also delivers a fantastic Mr. Charlie. At the same time, Keith adds that element that defines their 70s sound. There's a great dynamic happening between Keith's grand piano and Pigpen's organ on He's Gone. The songs are generally upbeat and catchy. There are some jams here as well such as China Cat Sunflower > I Know You Rider, Truckin' > Epilogue, and Prelude > Morning Dew. You can't go wrong with this album. It's long enough to capture the essence, but every song is superbly-executed. This is the album where they really start to coalesce into their 70s incarnation by transcending all of their influences to defy any category but the Grateful Dead.

product_name: Europe '72 [Live]
review_body: This is one of my favorite all time albums, by anybody. Every song a winner. At one time or another I have bought copies on vinyl, 8track, cassette, CD, reel to reel and digital download. If I could only have one Dead album this would be it. The only  thing some people don't like about it is that it isn't really that great a representation of their live sound as it was extensively overdubed. A few tracks have very little of the original live recording left. But the truth is that every record is an illusion, a representation if you will, of a fantasized version of a performer and this album is a perfect fantasy of a Grateful Dead concert circa 1972. If you want a better representation of what this would sound like without the dubs listen to the also excellent companion album Volume Two or of course the Europe 72 complete box set.

There's never been a band quite like them and its unlikely that there ever will be another. They were a unique American band that  changed people's' lives and this album contains some of the very best performances of those early post acid test years. I would never call them a folk band, but they were and remain a folk phenomena.

This results in some uneven browning, but I can live with that.If you want the front sponsons and the cockpit to come out right in the finished waffle, you do have to make sure you get some batter in those areas.  Which can be tricky with thick waffle batter.  Still, you'll get some expansion of the batter as the leavening kicks in, but it doesn't seem to fill these areas if there isn't any batter in them.Only thing I'd suggest changing about this iron is to not make that center hole quite so deep.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_title: cant egg za gerate how good this album is.
review_body: You must experience this album from the subhumans. Real punk. Real people. Real cool. like I said you must experience their music, read the lyrics thats what makes them what they are. their so good, that an exageration cannot top the truth.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_title: The punk rock "Sgt. Pepper." A multifaceted masterwork.
review_body: Arguably the Subhumans at their artistic peak.  This album shows that the  category "punk" is narrow and meaningless, for "From the  Cradle to the Grave" is quite able to stand alongside some of the  classic concept albums that were made ten to fifteen years before its  release, like The Who's "Sell Out" or Pink Floyd's "Dark  Side of the Moon".  Very impressive, both musically and lyrically.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_body: What to say? The Subhumans are just the best. And this is their best record. Albeit, other albums have more standout tracks (Time Flies/Rats specifically), but as a single coherent entity, "From the Cradle to the Grave" is the top of the heap. The lyrics are typically mind-blowing, and their musical approach is much more mature than the early days without losing their intensity (which, in my opinion, fizzled out with the lyrically breathtaking but musically stagnant "Worlds Apart"). If I were ever to get a band tattoo, it would be for these guys, despite the fact that their skull logo isn't the most impressive of artwork. That is about the strongest praise I can give. Blast it, devour it, make it your manifesto.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_title: Hands down, the best British punk album of all-time.
review_body: Yeah, I don't regret that title. This release is breathtaking, from the opening fifty second long instrumental to the final sixteen-minute title track that ranks among the ten greatest songs ever recorded by anyone, regardless of genre. It's not just Dick's lyrics, brilliant as always, that make this album a classic, but also the music, constantly changing pace and tone, from the upbeat ska/reggae of "Us Fish Must Swin Together" to the threatening "Wake Up Screaming" to the relentless "Reality Is Waiting For A Bus." And then there's the title track, combining the best of all genres of music the Subhumans ever experimented with, tied together by wonderful lyrics and a dozen catchy riffs that disappear almost as soon as they appear, perhaps never to return. And, best of all, the filler that plagued past Subhumans releases ("Zyklon-B-Movie," "Powergames" and almost the entire Time Flies E.P, to name a few) is nowhere to be found. Buy it now, you definitely will not regret it.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_title: The Anarcho Punk Equivilent To "Dark Side of The Moon"
review_body: This album is sheer briliance. In my opinion, its Subhumans best. From the 1st instrumental track, to the final, mesmorizing title track... you'll see why subhumans are considered such a great british punk band. This album also showcases their tremendous musical ability. Its not 3 chord dribble like others (namely the sex pistols), its well constructed music with a message. Buy this album, it will not dissapoint.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_title: the best punk band from england ever!!!!!!!!!!!
review_body: From the Cradle to the Grave is in my opinion, the best punk album ever.From start to finish this album never let's you down.the talent is unbelievable, and the song structures are perfect. i have this on 12" vinyl, and it is one of my favorite albums. the only other punk band on the Subhumans level is the Dead Kennedys, but they're great anyway. BUY THIS ALBUM EVEN IF YOU DON'T REALLY LISTEN TO ALOT OF PUNK ROCK. YOU WON'T REGRET IT!!!!!!!!!  top 5 albums  5.Slint-Spiderland  4.Subhumans-From the Cradle to the Grave  3.The Minutemen-Double nickels on the Dime  2.Dinosaur Jr.-Your living all over me  1.Sonic Youth-Daydream Nation or Paul's boutique by the Beatie boys

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_body: Green Day get all the credit for "American Idiot", but the Subhumans already made a punkrock opera 20 years (!) earlier."From the Cradle to the Grave" Is a cross between traditional old school punk and Progressive Rock. They made it work. They were very talented musicians for punks (this is a faaaar cry from The Ramones) and this is maybe their highlight. The only thing that makes this punk is the Cockney Accent of the Singer.The songs are awesome, and oooh man those titles! "Reality is waiting for a bus", "us fish must swim together", and off course the 17 minute title track "From the cradle to the grave". thats SEVENTEEN minutes, Green Day eat your heart out!

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_title: WICKED BRITISH PUNK ROCK CONCEPT ALBUM
review_body: Whaaaaaa? British Punk concept, in the same sentence? I don't remember how or why I got started into listening to SUBHUMANS. They are quite a different band that what I usually listen to, but nowadays (girl I know unloaded ALL of her Subhuman albums on me) I have every single album.I pick 'em up now and again. I like punk rock, but certain times more than others. SUBHUMANS have a rich british punk sound that is always enjoyable, so, yeah.. I dig it.My favorite album is definately this one.. FROM CRADLE TO THE GRAVE, a concept album about life, living life, hating life, loving life.. and death.I don't know how that sounds to you. This review has already gotten way to technical....JUST PLAY IT REALLY LOUD WHEN YOU'RE GETTING DRUNK! Five punk rock stars.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_body: This albums just never seems to grow old. As English punk goes this is amongst my favorite band. Subhumans deliver great great lyrics, rythmic tunes filled with melody yet wonderfully dischord and loud. Blending speedy punk and a reggae style is their signature.

product_name: Cradle to Grave [Vinyl]
review_body: subhumans were always one of the best of the anarcho bands from the early 80's.this , their second full length, see's them with a fuller production and more structured song writing than on earlier releases.I remember seeing them live at around the time of this l.p's releaseand they played the title track in it's 16 minute entirety as thefinale of their set. this album brought back fond memories for me. Agreat record by a great band, who are still as good now as they were way back then. check out their "live in a dive" cd if you need proof.buy thisyou won't regret it.

review_title: Cool item, could use a few adjustments and would be great!
review_body: Using Alton Brown's buttermilk waffle recipe from Good Eats Vol 2 (the book) -I really like the concept.  Here are the issues I have with this product, your mileage may vary:1: The plates are too large.  The resulting waffles will not fit in a standard toaster for reheating.  If the plates were reduced in diameter by about an inch, that would be perfect.2: The lands and grooves do not have enough separation - this reduces the cooking surface area and prevents the waffles from crisping up in the iron, even with the heat control set at max.Those are the two problems with it that need fixing.  If they fix them, they could also make the total distance between the low points on both the upper and lower plates a touch further from each other.With those two adjustments, I'd probably give this unit a five star review.

product_name: Star Wars Death Star Waffle Maker
review_body: While it does make a waffle that has the Death Star imprinted on it, the waffles are incredibly thin.  The coolness factor of this item does not outweigh the fact that this is not a very good waffle iron.Despite the waffles being thin, it takes quite a long time for a waffle to be cooked on it.  It's also VERY easy to put too much batter onto the iron and make a huge mess, with batter that drips down inside the machine.The lid isn't very heavy (despite the description saying it's a weighted lid) and I found I had to put something heavy on top to keep the top plate from rising too much once the waffle (finally) starts to cook.After a few uses, I had to disassemble it to clean the batter out from inside the maker and I wound up breaking some of the plastic molded pieces trying to re-assemble the unit.  A very cheap design and you need to be careful not to put too much batter in this maker.

product_name: Star Wars Death Star Waffle Maker
review_body: Cute and a fun idea! I grew up with a dad who loves Star Wars and would make us waffles ever Sunday. For his birthday, I got him this and a Darth Vader apron. He loved the idea! However, he was disappointed when he made the first batch. They were so thin and the grooves werenâ€™t deep enough to let the batter get fluffy and crispy like a waffle. It was more of a dense pancake. Still cute though!

product_name: Star Wars Death Star Waffle Maker
review_title: Green light doesn't work...doesn't brown...wouldn't buy again.
review_body: OK...So this doesn't brown your waffles the way the picture shows. Only the middle gets brown and the rest stays pale cream color. Also, the green light on top doesn't work so you have no idea when it is done. The orange light stays on all the time and the green one doesn't light up when done. The overall concept is cool. My son loves the death star waffle design regardless but I would love for it to work properly...I wouldn't buy it again. It gets two stars instead of one because my son likes the design.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: I have been researching home security cameras for a long time (months). I was considering buying the original Arlo cameras but decided I wanted to go with the Arlo Pro 2 to get a full 1080P resolution. These cameras perform very well and have helped us monitor our home remotely for the last month and a half. Arlo sensitivity is amazing and we have been able to keep an eye on our home inside and out with the phone app. I would definitely recommend Arlo Pro 2 to anyone that wanted a quality camera to monitor their home. BTW the battery life has been amazing as one of the cameras still has 80% battery life after almost 2 months of use according to what the Arlo App is telling me as well as using the live video occasionally to make sure it is still working.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: For the price, this is one of the best home security monitoring devices. The Arlo Pro 2 (3 Pack), not to be confused with the Arlo Pro 2 Pack, provided me with coverage of the 3 major entry points to my home with a 1080p resolution. The motion sensors have caught every person walking up.  My only issue is license plate capturing, which cannot be done without 4K resolution (understandable), but this provides peace of mind for sure! Also, the 100 decibel siren is a perfect addition to this system. Loved the app and the free cloud storage, compared to Nest. I do own a Nest thermostat but you cannot beat Arlos value AND the compreable picture resolution!

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_title: Love them. Easy to set up
review_body: Love them. Easy to set up. Picture quality is great. Work great plugged in or not. Donâ€™t hesitate. These are the easiest system to use.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: We spent a significant amount of time researching all the systems out there and chose the ARLO system.  The images are extremely clear and it offers the flexibility of additional cameras.  It was very easy to install.  We would highly recommend this system.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: Great picture and easy to set up

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: Excellent quality and easy installation. Lots of online operational training videos available. Cameras are VERY good and night vision much better than expected.  I'm not giving test specs, just observations from my experience. I bought four cameras for outdoor security viewing of my home property. They are so good and the field of vision so extensive (130 degrees) that I'm having difficulty deciding where I want the other two units placed. The Wi-Fi signal is very good and covers my entire 3200 sq ft. home area.  A signal extender is optional. The Internet response with free Basic service is excellent. I researched a lot of system and they all require compromises. For my needs the ARLO Pro 2 was the best and I'm pleased with the installation, so far.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: Simple simple and simple to install!

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: easy to install. easy to use.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_body: Camera quality is very good.  I'm not a huge fan of the included magnetic mount --- the magnets seem strong enough, but how the mount attaches to the wall doesn't seem very stable.  I will likely purchase a pack of more stable mounts.  I've seen complaints about the base station, but I had no issues with it.  The 7 days of free cloud storage is HUGE.  Competitors offer 1 day, which just isn't enough.  So far I'm an Arlo fan.

review_title: Better cameras than first gen, with better features.
review_body: I am very pleased with the Arlo Pro 2. I have had the original Arlo system for over two years and have been overall satisfied. I upgraded for a few major reasons: rechargeable batteries, direct power, pre-three second recording when plugged in to AC, local USB recording, two-way audio. I have not had any issues with the Pro 2â€™s and very satisfied with all of the new features.The Pro 2 have a slightly better viewing angle and the 1080p is nice, but I thought the 720p wasnâ€™t bad at all. I do have two Pro cameras with the four Pro 2â€™s, so i have done the comparison. I did not need to pre-three second recording, 1080p, and zone capabilities and went cheap with just the two add-on Pro cameras. The capability to mix/match camera with each of the base station is a plus. Night vision is slightly better on the PRo 2â€™s. (See images:  enclosed patio with no lights, driveway with some outside lights, and backyard with no lights - all cameras are about 10-12 feet high.)So far, I have not had the unexpectedly disconnecting issue as mentioned in other reviews. I was told that a higher internet upload speed/bandwidth is required with the Pro 2 due to the higher resolution. As mentioned on the specs, up to 2 mbps per camera is recommended. I have gigabit internet and the email alerts arrive just as fast as the original Arlo cameras. This tells me the captured video is uploading to the Netgear cloud storage without delays. I like Arloâ€™s alerting and notification options and scheduling flexibility. So far, Arloâ€™s (first gen., Pro, or Pro 2) is a better security system overall compared to Ring and Nest.

product_name: Arlo Pro 2 by NETGEAR Home Security Camera System (3 pack) with Siren, Wireless, Rechargeable, 1080p HD, Audio, Indoor or Outdoor, Night Vision, Works with Amazon Alexa (VMS4330P)
review_title: Flawless Installation, Motion Detection Could Be a Bit Better
review_body: Installation and setup was flawless, exactly as the directions described (for my situation, my phone, etc.). I picked this camera for the good reviews and past success with Netgear products. An important feature for me was quality motion detection so I installed the cameras so they would have wired power. I have a weak wifi signal where the cameras are located but I get an OK signal from the Netgear base station, a pleasant surprise since the base is located next to my router. The picture is sharp and clear and the free 7 days of recording is nice. The clips that are sent to the cloud back up a few seconds prior to the motion detection trigger, a nice feature. I did happen to see something real time within the defined trigger zone that didn't get captured. Not sure why or how often it happens since it triggers whenever I wander into the detection zone. So why 4 stars instead of 5? They give you 3 rectangles to define the detection zone that doesn't give me the flexibility I need/want to define my zone and exclude areas that get motion that I don't care about. I had a system in a previous house that laid the camera view on a checkerboard with small squares that you could click on to define your zone. That wasn't perfect either but it was a lot closer than this. On the plus side they do seem to be able to filter out (reasonably well) plants blowing in the wind and shadow changes with the time of day. I'm happy, no regrets, would have given it 4 and a half stars if I could. Maybe a future upgrade will enhance the detection zone (or maybe not).

review_body: I ordered this because I inherited a house from my father after he passed. The house is in another state 4 hours away, so I canâ€™t just pop over to check on it. His ex-wife moved in with him before he passed away (long story). I had to go to court to enforce his will and evict her from the property. This whole process took months as the courts move slowly. After the eviction, I could finally enter the house and I learned that most of his valuables were stolen. We kept getting reports from the neighbors that questionable people were hanging around the property and load up trailers with his things. I set up the Arlo cameras to catch anything that happens after the eviction. Several blind spots became apparent after I realized that she had broken back into the house and stole more things. I bought another camera to help with blind spots, but there is simple too much space that the cameras donâ€™t detect. The reason I left a 4 star review instead of a 5 star review is because of the limitations of the motion detection. My father had 11 acres, which Iâ€™m not trying to cover everything, but the house, garage, and barn are spaced further apart than the Arlo Pro 2 can cover. Other than this issue, the cameras work great!

product_name: Angelus Brand Acrylic Leather Paint High Gloss Finisher No. 610 - 4oz
review_body: I applied this to a pair of leather boots hoping to bring out the shine of the leather. I was surprised that there was a product that would permanently adhere to leather and maintain a shine, but I was excited to try it. Well, unfortunately my skepticism was well-merited because while this product did deliver a shine, it was short lasting and easily ruined.I applied several coats of the product, making sure that it dried in between coatings. I noticed right away that it had a little bit of a tack to it. I hoped that tack would go away but it never did. As a result, the boots are now a magnet for debris. Kind of ruins the shine when everything sticks to them. On top of that, the coating is pretty fragile and flakes off easily. As some people have mentioned, it goes on white but dries clear. Well, that's true until it gets scuffed or worn - then it goes right back to an opaque white wherever any tiny abrasion occurs, and with boots, that happens often. If someone stepped on these boots, there'd be a semi-permanent shoe mark on them. What a joke!It's true this product makes things shine and it gives it that wet look, but it comes at a cost of losing the durability of the original material. This product behaves exactly as one would expect acrylic paint to behave - flexible but non-durable and not well suited for clothing.

product_name: Angelus Brand Acrylic Leather Paint High Gloss Finisher No. 610 - 4oz
review_title: My now preferred sealer on the leather accessories I produce and sell
review_body: Amazon you really do a dis-service to the leather related servicre products asking how they "fit" for your product reviews. This product is so outstanding in the application process compared to the acrylic resolene that is manufactured by a major competitor. This Angelus product goes on the Latigo strips I use in such a streak free maner, I have just disposed of the gallon container I had in stock and this stuff is not cheap. Speaking of price, I am disappointed that quantities of more than 4 ounces are carried here at my favorite place to shop personal as well as business. But in this case dance a larger quantity is not available, I found that Angelus sells direct on the internet. The prices are better but they do not offer free shipping. All in all, a much better deal from Angelus and their products including  their dye and paint ROCK!

review_title: High Gloss Only Because It Is Not Matte
review_body: I bought this to seal over Angelus red shoe-bottom paint, in effort to restore some Louboutin's I have. Since this product is supposed to be "high gloss", I guess I actually expected a seriously shiny... wait for it... high gloss finish.Sadly, I was disappointed in the lack of gloss! I followed the instructions for application on one (pre-cleaned) shoe first. I didn't see the high gloss finish once the shoe was dry, so I chalked this up to user error. Upon re-reading the instructions and checking Google for application tips/tricks, I went ahead and completed the other shoe of the pair. Still not how I expected "High Gloss"  to appear once it was dry. The shoes look better than they did before, just not high gloss, really.After that, I tried the same application (over the red-bottom paint) on a few other leather-soled shoes, but with a few variations, feeling like I still must not be doing something correctly. I tried light sanding in between coats (similar to how one would refinish/paint wood, or anything that required excellent adhesion). Nope. I tried adding extra coats. No dice.I've come to the conclusion that a water-based product can't produce a real "high gloss" shine, and in this case, the finish this product provides is more gloss than the finish from their matte finish product, so was named accordingly.

product_name: Samsung Chromebook 3, 11.6", 4GB RAM, 16GB eMMC, Chromebook (XE500C13-K04US)
review_body: Multiple issues with the Chromebook.  I want to start this review off by saying that I'm an educator and have been using my Acer Chromebook for over 5 years and it still works great.  The Chromebooks my school uses (not Samsung) also have very few problems.  I bought this Samsung 3 Chromebook on Black Friday from a big box store with the plans to pass my older machine off to my teenager.  The first thing I noticed was that the sound quality is horrible on this compared to my five year old Acer.  One night I was watching Amazon Prime movies and the battery was getting low so I plugged my Samsung Chromebook 3 in to the charger it came with and went to bed.  In the morning I wanted to finish my movie and when I turned it back on the screen was messed up.  I contacted Samsung and described the screen as being blotchy.  They told me there was a 1 year warranty and to send it in.  I did and a week later I got a message saying that the LCD screen was broken and it violated the warranty.  I questioned how I broke it given it was working 100% fine, I plugged it in and set it on a desk to charge, and nobody touched it besides myself (charging in my room).  They said they'd fix it for $168 which is more than I paid for it.  I declined and it was sent back.  I just ordered a generic LCD screen from Amazon and fixed it myself in under 5 minutes.  The generic screen was $32.  I am completely disgusted with Samsung.  This is the fourth product from Samsung that I have had issues with ($3600 designer fridge, $1500 laundry pair, and also a microwave$350 microwave).  I've had extended protection warranties on all my other Samsung purchases, but due to the nature of having to buy quick for Black Friday (sells out in seconds) I didn't get an extra warranty.  I will never buy Samsung anything again.  I definitely would not buy this again.

product_name: SoundPEATS Magnetic Wireless Earbuds Bluetooth Headphones Sport In-Ear Sweatproof Earphones with Mic (Super sound quality, IPX6, Bluetooth 4.1, aptx, 8 Hours Play Time, Secure Fit Design) - Black
review_body: I use these earbuds while I'm on the treadmill.  I like to watch TV while I run on the treadmill but I miss a lot.  These earbuds solve that issue.  I have a bluetooth adapter I plug into the TV's audio port since this TV is the older one in the gym room.  The earbuds connect to the adapter with a simple procedure (Press and hold the button on the adapter until it blinks, press & hold the button on the earbuds until the earbud lights blink, wait a few seconds and they automatically connect with each other and both lights quick blinking).  The quality is good and the volume +/- is easy to use.  The battery life has been wonderful. I use these about 30 minutes every other day and I only need to charge them about once every few weeks.  Very happy with purchase.

review_body: Sounds great but does not work well for telephone conversations. People have a hard time hearing me. I can't use it for hands free phone calls while I drive which is a big reason I got them.

product_name: TaoTronics Bluetooth Headphones Wireless In Ear Earbuds Sports Earphones with Microphone, Black (8 Hours Playtime, Bluetooth 4.1, Hands Free Calling, Maximum Compatibility)
review_body: We went through four of these in a 15 month time period if that tells you anything.  We were able to get a replacement for two pair but the last two, no dice.  They begin to not sync with any bluetooth device.  Then it won't recharge and eventually just dies.  This happened on all of ours.  You would think after FOUR times they'd realize their product is not good and at least offer our money back.  Don't waste your money or trouble on this product.  We have learned!
